manufacturerProductDescription.media_text: Lightning X Fully Stocked TacMed Backpack PB89-SKM PB89 Tactical Backpack w/ Trauma & Bleeding Fill Kit The LXPB89 is a compact backpack style first responder kit featuring four main exterior compartments plus a quick access compartment behind the lumbar panel. The front, sides and bottom feature modular (MOLLE) loops for attaching extra gear. The back of the main compartment includes a zippered pouch designed to hold a hydration pouch. The shoulder straps are completely adjustable from all points to accommodate different body types and also feature a chest strap, and webbing loops to hold a drinking tube. The rear of the bag is designed with padded mesh lumbar panels to make long periods of wear more comfortable on your back. Inside the main two compartments are smaller mesh panels that are perfect for organizing your gear and keeping items separated. Every opening consists of extra large dual zippers with corded zipper pulls for easy opening and closing of compartments.

Stay Emergency Ready You'll be ready to respond to emergency situations with plenty of supplies for CPR, airway, bruises, bumps, sprains, trauma, bleeding, bandaging, wrecks, broken bones, cuts, scrapes, wound cleansing, burns, cardiac & blood pressure diagnostics, kids boo-boo's, bar fights & even that 5-car pile up that's making you late to work. Have you ever purchased a first aid kit with 589,234 pieces and felt like you got ripped off? Our kit includes over 250 items that you'll actually use. We don't "pad the numbers" with tons of bandages to make it seem like you're getting more in your kit. Our staff includes former EMT's who (between sweeping the floors and taking out the trash) help design our kits with real-world supplies. Our kit comes stocked with the following items: ● Tweezers ● Kelly Hemostats ● Trauma Sheers ● Bandage Sheers ● LED Penlight ● Ammonia (10) ● Heavy-Duty Adhesive Bandages (100 assorted sizes) ● 4" x 4" Gauze Pads (50) ● 2" Roll Gauze (2) ● 3" Roll Gauze (2) ● 4" Roll Gauze (2) ● 2" Self-Adherent Bandage (2) ● 2" Elastic Ace Bandage (2) ● 5" x 9" ABD Pad (2) ● 8" x 10" ABD Pad (2) ● 1" Roll Cloth Tape ● Iodine Wipes (10) ● Isopropyl Alcohol Wipes (10) ● Triple Antibiotic Ointment 1/2 oz ● Instant Cold Packs (2) ● Eye Pads (2) ● Triangle Bandage (2) ● Eye Wash Irrigation Solution ● Nitrile Exam Gloves (4) ● Universal SAM Finger Splint ● Oral Glucose Gel ● Adult Blood Pressure Cuff w/ Case ● Sprague Stethoscope ● CPR Mask ● Berman Airway Kit (6 sizes) ● Sting & Bite Relief Swabs (10) ● 4" x 4" Burn Dressing (2) ● First Aid Guide ● Quick Clotting Hemostat Gauze 4" x 4" (2) ● Dyna-Stopper Trauma Pressure Dressing ● 12" x 30" Multi-Trauma Pad ● Compressed Z-folded Gauze 4.5" x 4.1yd ● Israeli Pressure Bandage 4" ● First Aid Spray 2oz ● Burn Spray 2oz ● Manual CPR Set ● 36" Universal Roll Splint ● Emergency Mylar Blanket.

Be Prepared To Make Anywhere Your Hospital The PB89 gear bag is designed to be mobile! With a reinforced carry handle and an adjustable, padded shoulder strap this gear bag and fill kit can go anywhere you go. Perfect for schools, sports, special events, camping, hiking, offices, warehouses, concerts, ball games, day cares, fire departments, rescue squads, POV's, helicopters, space ships, your ex's house... scratch that, you should probably stay away from there... Expertly Designed for Unmatched Quality Hook & Loop Patch The front panel includes three rows of hook & loop M.O.L.L.E storage loops. We give you a free American Flag morale patch, or add your own patch or department logo to further personalize your gear bag. Also great for storing trauma shears, window punches and permanent markers. Modular Dividers & Pockets The main compartment features removable foam storage dividers to easily organize your medical supplies. Multiple clear vinyl zippered pockets are great for adhesive bandages, gauze sponges and other flat items like chest seals and occlusive dressings. Multi-Sized Tool Storage Our front quick-access pocket includes two rows of double layer elastic loops in two different sizes so that your bag will accommodate virtually any sized tools. These loops are great for oral or nasal airways, trauma shears, pen lights, tweezers, med vials and more!
Tough, Lightweight, & Dependable Be Prepared! Stay "Emergency Ready" with your next stocked first aid trauma kit from Lightning X!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 23, 2022
reviews.reviewText: 200 hundred dollar of awesomeness. The bag is tuff and durable. This is my 7th purchase from this company and I haven't had any complaints. I bought this bag because it had the top flip clip thats can be used in my car. In my last picture I'm pointing it out. If you take that over your headrest and put the clip through the middle of the two bars, then tighten it will hold it perfectly against your seat.Perfect for traveling. I'd recommend also getting the bags as well. My set up is the main zip that lays flat has all my trauma gear. The second zip has my BP cuff, stethoscope, splints, wraps. The smaller zip were the velcro is perfect for storing gloves. The smaller molle zip has my pen lights, extra shears(2), and extra pads and rolls so I don't have to open the main compartment., also have my 2 of the folling pens, permanent markers, and note pads. The bags I call my fast bags, the blue one has all my burn gels, ice packs, and burn bandages. The yellow one is my ouch pouch basic first aid kit with Aspirin for hose headaches and MIs, also have band aids, wound cleaners, and glucose. The red bag has my cat tourniquets(3) ,Israeli bandages(2), bleed stop spray(1) and guazes(4), krinkle guaze(1), and chest seals (3). My green bag is all my airway, it has OPAs (6), NPAs(6), and has 02 tubing. I DO NOT carry O2 with me but when in traveling I know that the EMS does carry so I also have a Non rebreather mask Regular O2 mask and nasal cannula.****** Sone of the items I listed came from my other pack I have I do believe that was refill kit R. But from all my other purchases I have had all the following refill kitsKit R,J,X,P,L,B, and this kit from this purchase. I only have my three bags one for the car, my household one. And now a tactical bag that's smaller and less a pain to carry. I hope this review helped someone make this purchase or inspired you to follow this company and find a fit for you. I would like to say that I am not affiliated with this company in any way only as a satisfied customer and the main reason I keep purchasing from them.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 5, 2021
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Very impressed. Meds and bag are much better quality than the pictures!
reviews.reviewText: I did a lot of research, and even spent an hour going though this product with my sister who is a medical nurse.Not only does this check all the boxes and come with a great bag, but the quality of the medical materials is very good! I was originally hesitant, but after sorting the packages, and even breaking the seal on a few duplicate items to assess quality I've been very impressed. Many items are name brand, the rest are their "Lightning products" brand which seems to be very comparable. NONE of the items seem to be low quality or something I would not want to use in an emergency.Bag is water resistant and is made of a plastic lined material, comfortable padding/adjustment when worn, Molle and sealing "military" zippers is a huge plus as well. (pic)Although I feel most any 'normal' circumstance is fully covered and then some, I went the extra step and wanted to include treatment for more grizzly wounds such as working with chainsaws, machinery, and firearms. I added:- MOST IMPORTANTLY a headlamp. 50% of earth's rotation is night, every medkit needs a hand-free light!- Permanent Marker- *Additional individual sterile gloves- *Second Fishing Forceps- Medline 35 Wide Skin Stapler- SAM Bleeding Control Kit (Better for heavy bleeds and better *tourniquet)- *SAM Chitosan Hemostatic Dressing (Better bandage for large wound clotting)- *SAM Chest Seals (lung puncture "sticker" to seal/stabilize against collapsing)- *Additional Israeli bandages for wrapping- Petroleum bandages for continued care on healing wounds- *Antiseptic Silvasorb Silver Hydrogel for continued care- *Additional Israeli bandages- Saline Wash* Items in kit but purchased separately for additional quantity or better qualityAlso to note. Everything will fit in the bag EXCEPT the Pulmonary Resuscitator, CPR Mask, Stethoscope, and Blood pressure cuff will NOT! You'll want a separate (similar sized) bag for those items as even when unpackaged they are too bulky and either don't fit at all, or would require displacing large amounts of the other items.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 3, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Good kit, a little too small for my taste.
reviews.reviewText: Good kit, pretty well stocked for every emergency. A little too small if you want to add anything else. I have already hung a couple of separate bags on mine. Will probably buy another bag with more pockets and room for a backpack suction unit. Nice bag though, very well built.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on May 3, 2018
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars A great basic kit at a good price with almost anything you might need.
reviews.reviewText: Just about everything you could possibly need, and at a great price too. I've put together very expensive jump bags in the past. This is superb for almost anything you need for a personal bag in the car as a medic, first-responder, EMT, or paramedic.I added a couple more airway items (chest seals, tension pneumo dart) as well as a short board and straps. Also a pulse oximeter. All fits just perfectly in the trunk.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 9, 2020
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Incredible Emergency Med Kit! I Feel Prepared :D
reviews.reviewText: This is the first true medical kit I have ever purchased. I purchased it at the start of the coved pandemic because I had seniors to take care of at home. This is one of the most complete med sets I have ever seen. It’s great. There’s so many supplies I almost can’t get it all in the backpack. The backpack is made well and can be used for outdoors. However, the fabric is not completely waterproof. With much gratitude, thank you, and hope this helps others. :DPros:1) A comprehensive set of supplies2) Quality products3) Well packaged4) The backpack is good quality material and well builtCons:1) No instructions on which items are best put together in the backpack2) Backpack not completely waterproof
